claim.claim-text:
1. An apparatus for monitoring wavelength multiplexed signal light containing multi-channel optical signals having different wavelengths from each other within a transmission band, said apparatus comprising: 
an input waveguide; 
an output waveguide; 
an monitoring waveguide; 
optical branching means provided between the input and output waveguides for branching a part of the signal light to the monitoring waveguide; 
a controllable optical filter provided on said monitoring waveguide that gives a loss pattern to said optical signals; and 
light-detecting means provided at an output end of the monitoring waveguide.

4. An apparatus for monitoring wavelength multiplexed signal light according to claim 3, wherein the number of said optical signals is N (N being an integer not less than 2); 
the number of said loss patterns is N; and 
N sets of said monitored data for said optical signals are obtained from N sets of said data detected for the respective loss patterns.

14. A method of monitoring wavelength multiplexed signal light according to claim 13, wherein the channel number of the optical signals is N (N being an integer not less than 2); 
the number of said loss patterns is N; and 
N sets of the monitored data for the optical signals are obtained from N sets of the detected data for the respective loss patterns.
